From 1a11d5d4384e0ff13690e377391ec40a563e744e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karthikeya <karthi@jovio.in>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 05:15:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat(observability): Sentry error tracking on api +
 pipeline
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Without error tracking we'd be blind to call failures in prod. Adds
@sentry/node (api) and sentry-sdk[fastapi] (pipeline). Both no-op
when SENTRY_DSN env is empty so dev/CI environments aren't affected.

api-server (Node):
- Sentry imported and Sentry.init() called BEFORE any other import so
  it can instrument Express, HTTP, and the underlying http.Server
- Sentry.setupExpressErrorHandler mounted AFTER all routes
- 10% trace sample rate (perf), 100% error capture
- /health and /ready transactions filtered out (would flood traces)
- Fallback express error handler returns clean 500 JSON instead of
  Express's HTML error page

voice-pipeline (Python):
- sentry_sdk.init() with FastApiIntegration + LoggingIntegration
- WARNING+ logs become breadcrumbs, ERROR+ become events
- Safe try/except — pipeline keeps running if Sentry init fails
- 10% trace sample rate

env.example: SENTRY_DSN, NODE_ENV/JOVIO_ENV, RELEASE_SHA (optional —
set by CI for release tracking)
