From 25ecfe58463633576d9605f038d83b898dda0287 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karthikeya <karthi@jovio.in>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 05:15:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] feat(supabase): branded HTML email templates for auth
 flows
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Supabase default email templates look generic and trigger spam filters
more often (Bayesian filters flag the bare 'click this link' style).

Branded templates for:
  - confirm-signup.html  (post-signup email verification)
  - magic-link.html      (passwordless sign-in)
  - reset-password.html  (forgot password flow)
  - _shared_header.html  (inline SVG J mark + JOVIO wordmark for reuse)

Uses inline styles only — required for email-client compatibility
(Gmail strips <style> blocks; Outlook needs explicit table layout).
SVG J mark is inlined so it renders in every client.

Installation is dashboard-only (Supabase doesn't support template
sync via API yet). README.md in the folder walks through the paste
process + which other auth settings to configure (custom SMTP via
Resend, redirect URLs, etc).

These templates only use {{ .ConfirmationURL }} and {{ .Email }} —
the two safest Supabase template variables.
